<paragraph id="DD66D978FFA9C439FF7BFEDAFEBDC3E1" blockId="1.[136,1451,320,414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="177">
This species differs from the other 
<taxonomicName id="1AD9A2FBFFA9C439FE27FEDAFD9AC306" box="[468,637,356,378]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phanerochaetaceae" genus="Ceriporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="1" pageNumber="177" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="EFAD056AFFA9C439FE27FEDAFDD4C305" box="[468,563,356,377]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="177">Ceriporia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by its combination of salmon basidioma, large angular pores (1 
<emphasis id="EFAD056AFFA9C439FB28FEDAFB14C305" box="[1243,1267,356,377]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="177">–3</emphasis>
per mm) and small ellipsoid spores.
</paragraph>
